Two separate issues here:

## 1. `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource`

`StaticResource` resolves **once** at load time. For runtime theme changes you must use `DynamicResource`:

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update at runtime -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Updates when the ResourceDictionary changes -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by clearing and merging dictionaries:

```csharp
var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDictionaries.Clear();
mergedDictionaries.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

## 2. Activity restart on system dark mode toggle

Android destroys and recreates the `Activity` on configuration changes like `uiMode`. In your `MainActivity.cs`, add `UiMode` to `ConfigChanges`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                         | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                         | ConfigChanges.UiMode   // ← prevents restart
                         | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                         | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                         | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    bool useDark = e.RequestedTheme == AppTheme.Dark;
    var merged = Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    merged.Clear();
    merged.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
};
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` is the main culprit for colors not updating; missing `ConfigChanges.UiMode` causes the full restart.
